 I total, then, there are eight independent trigger circuits, tour for each sine wave of which two are for positive and two are for negative trigger levels. The pulse sequences A A B and B are used [only in the phase measurement. The pulse sequences A A B and B are primarily intended for amplitude determination although levels B and B are also used to define the two regions of the sine Waves R and R while A and A; pulse sequences are used for the automatic start-stop operation. 
 The present invention in its preferred embodiment provides means whereby the time delay At can be made llor the negative half cycle of the sine wave inputs A and B as well as the positive half cycle. Since it is possible to have an apparent negative time delay, a At and a At is measured with the true At obtained from the difference thereof. 
 The logic circuit At 14 shown comprising four AND gates 64-67 and one OR gate 74 implements the digital measurement of At L over the complete cycle of the sine Waves A and B. Furthermore, by utilizing the logic circuitry with two synchronized time bases f and f as shown in FIGURE 9, pulse overlap or confusion is prevented. The first AND gate 64 produces an output of 1 1 (A -Tf -f -R the second AND gate 65 produces an output of (ZZ'Bg'fg'Rz), the third AND gate 66 produces an output of (A -F -f -R and the fourth AND gate 67 produces an output of (Z -B -f -R The OR gate 74 will yield an output at any time an output appears at any of the AND gates 64 through 67. The At counter 17 will count pulses equal to 4At+ each period of the sine wave input. In mathematical terms, the circuitry embodying the At logic mechanizes the equation: 
